[01:19.56]	It may be thought we held him carelessly,
[01:22.76]	Being our kinsman, if we revel much:
[01:25.56]	Therefore we'll have some half a dozen friends,
[01:29.18]	And there an end. But what say you to Thursday?
[01:32.73]PARIS	My lord, I would that Thursday were to-morrow.
[01:36.21]CAPULET	Well get you gone: o' Thursday be it, then.
[01:39.35]	Go you to Juliet ere you go to bed,
[01:42.14]	Prepare her, wife, against this wedding-day.
[01:45.42]	Farewell, my lord. Light to my chamber, ho!
[01:48.56]	Afore me! it is so very very late,
